# Asset Manager — Rules Index

Project guidance is split into `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` for focused context. Cursor loads those automatically.

| Rule file | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `project-overview.mdc` | Product, roles, tech stack |
| `architecture.mdc` | Repo layout and folder roles |
| `code-formatting.mdc` | Coding style — one blank line between sections (never two) |
| `coding-standards.mdc` | TypeScript / React avoid list |
| `react-events.mdc` | React 19 form/input event types (`SubmitEvent`, not `FormEvent`) |
| `safety-guardrails.mdc` | Protected files, security |
| `add-tests-on-change.mdc` | When and where to add tests |
| `projectGoal.mdc` | Resume roadmap & priorities (**gitignored**, local only) |

## Rules index for `product` branch

| Rule file | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `product/product-overview.mdc` | Editions, three-layer model |
| `product/product-modularization.mdc` | Config, modules, widgets, repositories |
| `product/product-capabilities.mdc` | Roles & capabilities (v2) |
| `product/product-data-schema.mdc` | stock schemas, PostgreSQL only |
| `product/product-deployment-tenancy.mdc` | Deploy vs SaaS |
| `product/product-roadmap.mdc` | P0–P4 checklist |
| `product/product-git-workflow.mdc` | `main` / `product` / `feature/*` |

Edit the `.mdc` files in `.cursor/rules/` rather than duplicating long guidance here.